Create a checkbox in the modules from where you want to fetch data
The if block will hide the data when the existing customer is selected as no
but when we click on yes after that, the system automatically dont fetch data
but we can do that by using setCretieria only, by using the checkbox creted initially
just search for this check box and set its value as true or false 
it will execute the else block and the cretieria will be searched and thus we will get out output

//this was done because the clearCretieria function was not working, as this dont exist


existing_customer = ZDK.Page.getField("Existing_Customer").getValue();
Account = ZDK.Page.getField("Account_Group");
Contact = ZDK.Page.getField("Contact");
Account.setValue(null);
Contact.setValue(null);
if (existing_customer == "" || existing_customer == "No" || existing_customer == null) {
    Account.setCriteria("(Account_Name:equals:" + "0" + ")", { filterOnSearch: true });
    Contact.setCriteria("(Account_Name:equals:" + "0" + ")", { filterOnSearch: true });
} else {
    // // If no Account Name is selected, clear the filter and reset the Deal Names field to show all deals
    // console.log("No Account selected. Showing all deals.");
    // Account.clearCriteria();
    // Contact.clearCriteria();  // Clear the filter
    Account.setCriteria("(Dev_Check:equals:" + false + ")", { filterOnSearch: true });
    Contact.setCriteria("(Dev_Check:equals:" + false + ")", { filterOnSearch: true });
}
